-- Asian Stocks Advance on Greek Debt Talk Progress, Toyota Profit Forecast
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2012-02-08T00:12:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/japan-futures-australian-stocks-rise-on-greece-debt-talks-toyota-profit.html
Asian stocks rose for a third day as
 Greece ’s government edged closer to securing a bailout package
and Toyota Motor Corp. raised its profit forecast.  The MSCI Asia Pacific Index  climbed 0.4 percent to 125.44
as of 9:06 a.m. in  Tokyo .  Japan ’s Nikkei 225 Stock Average
gained 0.6 percent, while the broader Topix Index advanced 0.7
percent.  Australia ’s S&P/ASX 200 Index increased 0.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
